sentences: Pieter Jan Leusink (born April 5, 1958 in Elburg) is a Dutch conductor of classical music.
Pieter Jan Leusink (born April 5, 1958 in Elburg) is a Dutch conductor of classical music.

He founded the Stadsknapenkoor Elburg (Elburg City Boys' Choir) in April 1981 and founded three musical events in Elburg's  St Nicholas Church, a Festival of Lessons and Carols in December, J.S. Bach's St Matthew Passion (BWV 244) during the Easter season, and summer concerts in July and August.
